</small></small></td></tr></tbody></table><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><table style="text-align: left; width: 823px; height: 151px;" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0"><tbody><tr><td style="white-space: nowrap; vertical-align: top;"><br><table style="text-align: left; width: 277px; height: 73px;" border="0" cellpadding="2" cellspacing="2"><tbody><tr><td valign="top"><big><big><big><big><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(204, 204, 204);">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span><small><span style="color: rgb(255, 102, 0);"> &nbsp; Events</span></small><span style="color: rgb(204, 204, 204);"></span></span></big></big></big></big></td></tr></tbody></table><br><br><br></td><td><small style="font-weight: bold;"><small style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><font size="2"><small><br></small></font><span style="font-style: italic;"></span></small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-style: italic;"></span></span><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-style: italic;">2010 November 06</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; 114th FFA monthly interclub practice (and 10th anniversary)</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></small><small><small><span style="color: rgb(255, 0, 0); font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">(Revised 2010 Nov. 04)</span></small></small><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><small style="font-weight: bold;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></small><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">All
are invited to the 114th FFA monthly interclub Aikido practice on
Saturday, November 06. This series of joint monthly practice sessions
started in 2000. </span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">This month's meet also celebrates the 10th
anniversary of the monthly interclub practice activity. To mark this
milestone, therefore, this month's event will have the following
special format:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br></small><font size="2"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Click <a href="114Interclub.pdf">here</a> to download invitation/poster.<br>Click <a href="114Interclub.html" target="_blank">here</a> to view invitation/poster online.<br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span></font><small><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: underline;">I. PROGRAMME for 2010 Nov. 06:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">5:30 - 6:15 pm&nbsp; &nbsp;Registration</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">6:15 - 6:25 pm&nbsp;&nbsp; Assembly</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">6:25 - 6:30 pm&nbsp;&nbsp; Opening remarks by Marielle Macapawa, 5th dan</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">6:30 - 6:55 pm&nbsp; &nbsp;Warm-up and Ki exercises led by Tada Juku Manila (TJM / ACP)</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">6:55 - 7:10 pm&nbsp; &nbsp;Keiko segment led by JBAC </span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">7:10 - 7:25 pm &nbsp;&nbsp;Keiko segment led by Kiryukan </span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">7:25 - 7:40 pm &nbsp;&nbsp;Keiko segment led by MAC </span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">7:40 - 8:10 pm &nbsp;&nbsp;Embukai (eight dojos from PAPA, Aikido Philippines, and FFA will<br>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; demonstrate)</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Sequence:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;1. PAPA Group</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;2. Fudoshin Aikido club</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;3. Shinbu Dojo</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;4. Makiling Aikido Club - UPLB</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;5. Philippine Heart Center Aikido Club</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;6. Jitsuyo Bugei Aikido Club (JBAC)</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;7. Kiryukan dojo</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 8. Makati Aikido Club (MAC) </span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"></span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">8:10 - 8:15 pm &nbsp; Closing remarks by M.Macapawa and Photo session</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">8:20 pm&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Drinks and dinner</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: underline;">II. PRACTICAL DETAILS:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">MAT CONTRIBUTION: &nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">PhP100</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">DATE AND TIME:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Saturday, 2010 November 06</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">1800 hrs (6:00 p.m.)</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">THIS MONTH'S HOST:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Tada Juku Manila (TJM)</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">THIS MONTH'S VENUE:</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Aikikai Center of the Philippines (ACP),</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Club 650, 150 E. Rodriguez Jr. Ave (C-5 road), Libis, Quezon City*</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">ALL REGARDLESS OF ORGANIZATIONAL AFFILIATION ARE WELCOME. For more details, e-mail macaikido@yahoo.com or call 890-1976 or 77.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; text-decoration: underline;">III. * Getting there: STREET DIRECTIONS</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">A) DRIVING YOUR CAR</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Club
650 is on the right coming from the south (Makati/The Fort etc), beside
Shopwise and before the entrance to Eastwood. Coming from the the north
(UP/Ateneo/Blue Ridge area), take C-5 into Libis area and make a u-turn
a few hundred meters after the Jollibee/Delifrance outlet. There is
ample parking in front.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">B) USING PUBLIC TRANSPORTATION</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Club
650 is accessible via the jeeps that traverse C-5. From EDSA, get off
at the Ortigas intersection, take a jeep to the Ortigas-C-5
intersection, get off at C-5 and take a second jeep north towards
Eastwood. Club 650 will be on the right coming from the south</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">(Makati), beside Shopwise and before the entrance to Eastwood.</span></small><br><br><small><span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; font-weight: bold;"></span></small><font size="2"><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
  <span style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">Click <a href="114Interclub.pdf">here</a> to download invitation/poster.</span><br style="font-family: Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;">
</font> 
